Get a free API key, or log in to your existing account

USAGE
  c3x auth [flags]
  c3x auth [command]

EXAMPLES
  Get a free API key, or log in to your existing account:

      c3x auth login

      You can also log in at https://dashboard.c3x.dev

  Manually set the API key that your CLI should use. The API key can be retrieved from your account:

      c3x configure set api_key MY_API_KEY

  Regenerate your API key:

      Log in at https://dashboard.c3x.dev > select your organization > Settings

AVAILABLE COMMANDS
  login       Authenticate the CLI with your C3X account

FLAGS
  -h, --help   help for auth

GLOBAL FLAGS
      --debug-report       Generate a debug report file which can be sent to C3X team
      --log-level string   Log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal)
      --no-color           Turn off colored output

Use "c3x auth [command] --help" for more information about a command.
